titleStmt.title: An order of his highness the Prince of Orange
titleStmt.author: England and Wales. Sovereign (1694-1702 : William III)

notesStmt.note: Troops are to be marched out of towns in which elections are going on and are not to return to quarters till the election is over.--Steele.
At end of text: "Given at St. James's the fifth day of January 1688/9"
Date given according to Lady Day dating.
Reproduction of original in the Folger Shakespeare Library.
